File: Gender-based violence JOHANNESBURG - Gender-based violence continues to be a concern in South Africa. According to reports, the number of cases has increased since the loosening of lockdown stages. READ: GBV epidemic | Bloody week for SA women Some non-government organisations are calling on government to impose harsher sentences. While some victims claim they have lost faith in law enforcement agencies. GBV remains an epidemic in the country. Government says society as a whole needs to play its part in ending the scourge. You at home might be asking: what collective efforts are actually needed to end this. eNCA speaks to Founder and Director of the Masimanyane Women’s Rights International, Dr. Lesley-Ann Foster. Courtesy #DStv403 eNCA's Ayesha Ismail has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 eNCA's Silindelo Masikane has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 